-- 
South African President Zuma Asked to End ‘Fracking’, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-04-06T05:11:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/south-african-president-zuma-asked-to-end-fracking-business-day-reports.html
South African and international
scientists asked President  Jacob Zuma  to stop proposals to
extract gas using hydraulic fracturing, or so-called fracking,
Business Day said, citing a report by Luke Havemann, an energy
lawyer who compiled the document.  Zuma’s office in Parliament, the Petroleum Agency of  South
Africa  and Gold Associates, the environmental advisory company
that helped draft  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA) ’s application to explore
in the Karoo region, also received the report, the Johannesburg-
based newspaper reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  